==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*aiþa-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[eth|ēth]], Old Saxon [[eþ|ēþ]] (Dutch [[eed]]), Old High German [[eid]] (German [[Eid]]), Old Norse [[eiðr]] (Swedish [[ed]]), Gothic [[𐌰𐌹𐌸𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /a:θ/

===Noun===
'''āþ''' ''m''
# an [[oath]]
#:''he aþ swereþ þurh his selfes lif'': he swears an oath on his own life.  (Cædmon’s ''Metrical Paraphrase'')

